OL,3,C'Cramped' Bibby Stockholm rooms could
OL,4,Cviolate human rights, MPs warn
OL,6,F"There needs to be readily accessible
OL,7,Fassistance available to deal with the
OL,8,Fmedical and mental health consequences
OL,9,Fof what they have been through.
OL,10,FSupport services on the barge must be
OL,11,Fadequate to meet the needs of those
OL,12,Fhoused there, and if not that there
OL,13,Fare practical steps in place to allow
OL,14,Fthem to be accessed in the wider
OL,15,Fcommunity."
OL,17,FEarlier this week Home Secretary James
OL,18,FCleverly told the Home Affairs
OL,19,FCommittee he is "totally confident"
OL,20,Fthe Bibby Stockholm meets all legal
OL,21,Frequirements.
